38f022ba-2820-5e7d-bf1d-beb90c39a3f6,tg:rubgr:914,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"P.B. Adoration, N.G. The  ox seems to be missing. This seems also be the case (judging by the poor reproduction in H. [Hugo] KEHRER, Die Heiligen Drei Könige in Literatur und Kunst, 2 vols., Leipzig [Seemann], 1908/9, vol. II, 1909, p. 236, Abb. 276) in the Adoration by the Master of the Munich Life of the Virgin, in the Martinskirche at Linz a. Rh. [am Rhein] of 1463 (Look up Reiners for better repr.)[= Heribert Reiners, Die Kölner Malerschule, (Monographien zur Geschichte der christlichen Kunst ; 5), Mönchen Gladbach: Kühlen, 1925]. An engraving by the Master A.G. (Albrecht Glockendon??[sic]), of c. 1480, in Vienna, shows the head of an animal which might be an ox and just below & behind this the mouth of another animal.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>P.B. Adoration, N.G. The  ox seems to be missing. This seems also be the case (judging by the poor reproduction in H. [Hugo] KEHRER, Die Heiligen Drei Könige in Literatur und Kunst, 2 vols., Leipzig [Seemann], 1908/9, vol. II, 1909, p. 236, Abb. 276) in the Adoration by the Master of the Munich Life of the Virgin, in the Martinskirche at Linz a. Rh. [am Rhein] of 1463 (Look up Reiners for better repr.)[= Heribert Reiners, Die Kölner Malerschule, (Monographien zur Geschichte der christlichen Kunst ; 5), Mönchen Gladbach: Kühlen, 1925]. An engraving by the Master A.G. (Albrecht Glockendon??[sic]), of c. 1480, in Vienna, shows the head of an animal which might be an ox and just below & behind this the mouth of another animal.</content>
<documentation.title>heiligen Drei Könige in Literatur und Kunst</documentation.title>
